-- Greece's Eurobank posts Q2 loss as provisions weigh 
-- 
-- Fri Aug 29, 2014 10:48AM EDT
-- None



ATHENS, Aug 29 (Reuters) - Greece's third-largest lender by assets Eurobank <EURBr.AT> reported a 301 million euro ($396.81 million) loss in the second quarter as loan-loss provisions continued to weigh on its bottom line.

Analysts polled by Reuters were expecting the bank to post a loss of 238 million euros on average. Eurobank, 35.4 percent owned by Greece's HFSF bank rescue fund, said credit loss provisions fell to 455 million euros in the second quarter from 647 million in the same period a year earlier.